		<!-- Food. -->

		<category>
			<pattern>SUPPORT FOR FOOD</pattern>
			<template>
				Local support can be given for families who may need food but cannot afford it. Community organisations called 'food banks' can provide this support.
Support with food for babies and infants can be given for whose whho are either 10 weeks pregnant or have a child under 4 years old
For more information, type "food bank", or "infant support"
			</template>
		</category>
		
		<category>
			<pattern>food bank</pattern>
			<template>
				Food banks are community organisations that can help provide food tho those who may not be able to afford it.
Those who wish to use a food bank will usually need to get a referral.
This can be done through local referrer organisations
			</template>
		</category>

		<category>
			<pattern>infant support</pattern>
			<template>
				Free vitamins and Health Start vouchers for milk, fruit and vegetables and infant formula milk canm be provided to those who may need it for their child but cannot afford it
In order to be eligible for these benefits, one must also be claiming either:
Income Support
Income-based Jobseeker's Allowance
Income-related Employement asnd Support Allowance - but only if you're pregnant
Child Tax Credit - and your householf earns £16,190 a year or less
Pension Credit
Universal Credit - and your household earns £408 a month or less

Those who are under 18 and pregnant are eligible even if they do not get any of the above benefits
			</template>
